{"legislative_session": "2025A", "identifier": "SB25-054", "title": "Mining Reclamation & Interstate Compact", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": [], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "Water Resources and Agriculture Review Committee. The bill amends the \"Colorado Mined Land Reclamation Act\" and the \"Colorado Land Reclamation Act for the Extraction of Construction Materials\" to:\n\n\nContemplate the expedited issuance of reclamation-only permits to persons desiring to conduct reclamation-only operations after July 1, 2025 September 1, 2025 , on less than 5 acres; and\nUpdate restrictions and requirements concerning the posting and forfeiture of financial warranties relating to mine reclamation projects.\n\n\nThe office of mined land reclamation may not issue a reclamation-only permit to a designated mining operation.\n\nThe bill also enacts the \"Interstate Mining Compact\" and ratifies Colorado's membership in the associated Interstate Mining Commission.\n(Note: Italicized words indicate new material added to the original summary; dashes through words indicate deletions from the original summary.)\n(Note: This summary applies to the reengrossed version of this bill as introduced in the second house.)"}], "other_titles": [], "other_identifiers": [], "actions": [{"description": "Governor Signed", "date": "2025-05-16T06:00:00+00:00", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"executive\"}", "classification": ["executive-signature"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Signed by the Speaker of the House", "date": "2025-05-12T06:00:00+00:00", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Sent to the Governor", "date": "2025-05-12T06:00:00+00:00", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"executive\"}", "classification": ["executive-receipt"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Signed by the President of the